article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 59, Texas-San Antonio 49
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. (AP) -- Nate Bowie came off the bench to score 14 points Thursday night as Central Arkansas topped Texas-San Antonio 59-49 in a Southland Conference matchup. The hometown Bears (6-10, 1-2 SLC) had hot shooting hands in the game's first half, making 58 percent of their shots from the field -- 11-of-19 -- and gaining a 32-23 lead at intermission. But UCA's shooting accuracy fell off markedly in the second half, as did that of the Roadrunners (4-11, 0-2). The Bears made fewer field goals after the break -- 8-of-21 -- though they fired off more shots than they had in the first half, and their shooting percentage fell to 38, while UTSA dropped from 46 percent to 35 percent. In addition to his scoring, Bowie sparked his teammates with four steals. Mitch Reuter had 13 points for the Bears, and Frederick Campbell added 11. Andrew Francis and Melvin Smith shared the scoring honors for UTSA, with 12 points each, while Keith Spencer scored 11.
